description: Camp Henry is the location of 24 oTENTik cabins, available for rent year-round. Camp Henry includes a number of amenities including a store, a play area, washrooms and showers.
Camp Henry is named for the Boy Scout camp previously in place elsewhere at Point Pelee National Park. The original site was closed due to PCB contamination.
Photo is courtesy of the Government of Canada. Find the original at https://parks.canada.ca/pn-np/on/pelee/activ/otentik
